### Viewport Units

**Viewport units** size elements relative to the browser viewport.

---

### The Units

| Unit | Relative To | Example |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `vw` | 1% of viewport width | `100vw` = full width |
| `vh` | 1% of viewport height | `100vh` = full height |
| `vmin` | 1% of the SMALLER dimension | Useful for mobile |
| `vmax` | 1% of the LARGER dimension | Avoid on mobile |
| `svh` | Small viewport height (no URL bar) | `100svh` |
| `lvh` | Large viewport height (with URL bar) | `100lvh` |
| `dvh` | Dynamic viewport height (changes with UI) | `100dvh` |
| `vi` | 1% of viewport inline size | Text direction aware |
| `vb` | 1% of viewport block size | Text direction aware |

---

### Full Screen Sections

```css
.hero {
  width: 100vw;
  height: 100vh;
  /* Full viewport hero section */
}
```

---

### Mobile Viewport Units

On mobile, `100vh` includes the browser UI (URL bar):

```css
/* Old way - may be too tall on mobile */
height: 100vh;

/* Modern mobile-safe approach */
height: 100dvh;  /* Dynamic - adjusts when URL bar hides */
/* Or */
height: 100svh;  /* Small - always without URL bar */
```

---

### Typography with Viewport Units

```css
/* Responsive font size */
h1 {
  font-size: 5vw;  /* 5% of viewport width */
}
```

**Caution:** `5vw` on a 320px phone = 16px (OK), but on a 2560px monitor = 128px (too big!).

---

### Clamp with Viewport Units

```css
/* Min, preferred, max */
h1 {
  font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
}
```

---

### Practical Uses

```css
/* Full viewport hero */
.hero {
  height: 100vh;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

/* Half width sidebar */
.sidebar {
  width: 30vw;
  min-width: 200px;
}

/* Responsive square */
.square {
  width: 50vmin;
  height: 50vmin;
  /* Always square, fits screen */
}

/* Fixed bottom bar */
.bottom-bar {
  height: 60px;
  bottom: 0;
  width: 100vw;
}
```

> **Best Practice:** Avoid `100vw` when scrollbar may cause horizontal overflow. Use `100%` for most widths. Use `dvh` for mobile height.
